        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2186202657" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14753822515238712096">&quot;Fear and Trembling&quot; embraces the strange with one wicked arsenal of irrational (but noble) thoughts &amp; actions by the superb heroine. Her authentic recklessness captivates, no enamours, the reader. I had very strong feelings for this incredible novel because I lived EXACTLY the type of professional downward spiral that all but defeats you. Like a posher (!?!?) precursor to &quot;The Devil Wears Prada,&quot; the entire plot unravels within the confines of the claustrophobic and limiting Workplace. This is </span>
  <span id="freeText14753822515238712096" style="display:none">"Fear and Trembling" embraces the strange with one wicked arsenal of irrational (but noble) thoughts &amp; actions by the superb heroine. Her authentic recklessness captivates, no enamours, the reader. I had very strong feelings for this incredible novel because I lived EXACTLY the type of professional downward spiral that all but defeats you. Like a posher (!?!?) precursor to "The Devil Wears Prada," the entire plot unravels within the confines of the claustrophobic and limiting Workplace. This is an ugly child that you want to keep with you forever: it's really THAT wonderful.</span>
