<div id="review_3545678923" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3545678923" />
    <a title="Paul Ataua" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/33831018-paul-ataua"><img alt="Paul Ataua" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1407668489p2/33831018.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3545678923?book_show_action=true">Sep 12, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Paul Ataua" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Paul Ataua" href="/user/show/33831018-paul-ataua">Paul Ataua</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780312347321" href="/book/show/71453.Fear_and_Trembling">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3545678923" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12683151785628383604">Despite seeming a little exaggerated, Nothomb really touches on many of the aspects of an Asian culture that were quite prevalent in company culture in the past , and which still exist today to a lesser extent. In many years of working in Asia, I have seen that blind acceptance of authority, workers criticized for taking initiative, and have even experienced a case of one person, not particularly competent in any area, who was passed around from department to department for years, taken care of,</span>
  <span id="freeText12683151785628383604" style="display:none">Despite seeming a little exaggerated, Nothomb really touches on many of the aspects of an Asian culture that were quite prevalent in company culture in the past , and which still exist today to a lesser extent. In many years of working in Asia, I have seen that blind acceptance of authority, workers criticized for taking initiative, and have even experienced a case of one person, not particularly competent in any area, who was passed around from department to department for years, taken care of, until retirement. ‘Fear and Trembling’ is a comic swipe at a culture seen through the eyes of someone from another culture using their own culture as a yardstick of common sense. It’s OK and quite an easy read. I would be interested to find out if anyone knows of a book written by someone Japanese working in a western company, and how they felt about our messed up culture. That really would be interesting.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12683151785628383604" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


