              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9584631053376592928">One of my book club selections, this very small book ended up creating a solid two hours of discussion, thanks in large part to the book club member who chose it. Rather than discuss obvious questions....she pulled about a dozen &quot;themes&quot; from the book, like LOVE, DUTY, HONOR, EGO, etc and used those as a jumping off point for relating our experiences. Very compelling and very entertaining.</span>
  <span id="freeText9584631053376592928" style="display:none">One of my book club selections, this very small book ended up creating a solid two hours of discussion, thanks in large part to the book club member who chose it. Rather than discuss obvious questions....she pulled about a dozen "themes" from the book, like LOVE, DUTY, HONOR, EGO, etc and used those as a jumping off point for relating our experiences. Very compelling and very entertaining.</span>
